cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing efficient algorithms for the MapReduce framework, which is a distributed computing paradigm. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses sorting and searching algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper analyzes the theoretical properties of the MapReduce framework and its algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possibility as the paper aims to put the MapReduce framework on an equal theoretical footing with other parallel models. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but is mentioned in the paper as an application of the MapReduce algorithms designed for sorting and searching.
